commit.message:
Add uid of node call to instance variable names

This is needed to support expansion of node calls in
the definition of an array.

Apply slicing in IC3IA engine instances

Each IC3IA engine instance applies slicing to the transition system for
the property it is checking. This ensures that an engine instance only
shuts down if the sliced system contains unsupported features. Previously,
all instances would shut down if any property included unsupported features.

Normalize generated equations using proper context

commit.message:
Extend support for type constructor history

This commit adds support for universally quantified properties where
the type of the bound variable is built with the type constructor history.
It also desugars the history constructor in Lustre assertions.
